main event: A witness observed a long luminous object traveling at a very high speed in the sky on the evening of February 12, 1966.
interesting points: The object was first seen as a bright warm glow in the east before the witness noticed it traveling from west to east., The witness noted that the object split into parts before continuing east., The entire sighting lasted less than a minute with no sound emitted by the object., The witness wrote a report to Project Blue Book after seeing the unusual object., The case was investigated but no further information could be obtained.
witness description: The witness is a habitual star-gazer and a student of astronomy.
